Stovetop Macaroni and Cheese
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 1/2 c water
8 oz elbow macaroni
4 oz american cheese, shredded (1 c)
1/2 tsp dijon mustard
small pinch cayenne pepper
4 oz extra sharp cheddar cheese, shredded (1 c)
1/3 c panko bread crumbs
1 tbsp evoo
salt and pepper
2 tbsp grated parmesan cheese

Bring water and milk to boil in medium saucepan over high heat. Stir in pasta and reduce heat to medium low. Cook, stirring frequently, until macaroni is soft (slightly past al dente), 6-8 min. Add american cheese, mustard, and cayenne and cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is completely melted, ~1 min. Off heat, stir in cheddar until evenly distributed but not melted. Cover saucepan and let stand for 5 min. Combine panko, oil, 1/8 tsp salt, and 1/8 tsp pepper in 8" nonstick skillet until panko is evenly moistened. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until evenly browned, 3-4 min. Off heat, sprinkle parmesan over panko mixture and stir to combine; transfer to small bowl. Stir macaroni until sauce is smooth (may look loose but will thicken as it cools). Season with salt and pepper to taste. Transfer to warm serving dish and sprinkle panko over top. Serve immediately,


Notes: Use block of american from deli counter, not presliced.
